# Testing — Run Tests After Code Changes

## Principle

**Always run related unit tests after making code changes.** Tests must pass before considering a change complete.

## When to Run Tests

After changing any of the following, run the corresponding tests:

| Changed Area | Run Command |
|--------------|-------------|
| ViewModel (`*ViewModel.kt`) | `./gradlew test` or `./gradlew :app:testDebugUnitTest` |
| Repository, API, domain | `./gradlew test` |
| Any Kotlin/Java code | `./gradlew test` |

## Workflow

1. Make code changes
2. Run `./gradlew test` (or `./gradlew :app:testDebugUnitTest` for unit tests only)
3. Fix any failing tests before finishing
4. Do not merge or commit with failing tests

## Test File Location

Each ViewModel has a sibling test file in `app/src/test/`:
```
app/src/main/.../OtpViewModel.kt  →  app/src/test/.../OtpViewModelTest.kt
```

## Quick Command

```bash
./gradlew test
```
